tafsir[9]{c,v,t}:
  54,10,"Noah called unto His Lord saying: My people have overwhelmed me and they did not respond to me. So take retribution from them by a punishment that you send down on them."
  54,11,"So I opened the doors of the sky to continuous torrential water."
  54,12,"I burst open the ground and it became springs from which water gushed. The water coming down from the sky met with the water gushing from the ground for a matter that Allah had determined in eternity. Everyone was drowned besides those whom Allah saved."
  54,13,"I carried Noah on a vessel that had planks and nails and I saved him and those with him from drowning."
  54,15,"I have left this punishment that I meted out to them as a lesson and admonition. Is there anyone to take a lesson from that?"
  54,16,"How was my punishment to those who denied? How was my warning that I will destroy them?"
  54,19,"I sent on them a severe cold wind on a day of evil and misfortune that will continue with them until they arrive in Hell."
  54,20,"It picked up people from the ground and threw them on their heads as if they were the trunks of date-palms uprooted from their plantations."
  54,21,"So reflect- O people of Makkah - how was my punishment to them? And how was my warning to others about their punishment?"